definition.value: A common and naturally occurring pyrimidine nucleobase in which the pyrimidine ring is substituted with two oxo groups at positions 2 and 4. Found in RNA, it base pairs with adenine and replaces thymine during DNA transcription.
An  N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl group obtained formally by removal of the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.
